      "type": "intro",
      "title": "Essential Lighting Requirements for Uromastyx",
      "content": "Uromastyx are full-sun baskers that require strong UVB and bright visible light. Proper lighting supports vitamin D3 synthesis, bone health, appetite, and natural activity."
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "heading": "UVB Requirements"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Aim for a basking UVI of 4.5-6.0 with a strong gradient that lets the lizard self-regulate."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "<span class='text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white block mb-2'>UVB Targets:</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "Parameter",
        "Target Value",
        "Measurement Location"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "UVI (UV Index)",
          "4.5-6.0",
          "Basking surface"
        ],
        [
          "Ferguson Zone",
          "Zone 4",
          "Full-sun basking species"
        ],
        [
          "Coverage Area",
          "50-70% of enclosure",
          "Warm side"
        ],
        [
          "Shade access",
          "Required",
          "Cool side and hides"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "warning",
      "severity": "important",
      "content": "High-output UVB is essential. Weak UVB or short fixtures are a leading cause of metabolic bone disease in Uromastyx."
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "heading": "UVB Equipment Selection"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Use a T5 HO linear UVB fixture with a 12-14% bulb that spans roughly half the enclosure length."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "<span class='text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white block mb-2'>Recommended UVB Types:</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "Bulb Type",
        "UVB Output",
        "Length",
        "Replacement Interval"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "T5 HO high output",
          "12-14%",
          "Half enclosure length",
          "12 months"
        ],
        [
          "T5 HO mid output",
          "10%",
          "Half enclosure length",
          "10-12 months"
        ],
        [
          "T8 linear",
          "Not preferred",
          "Longer length needed",
          "6-8 months"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "warning",
      "severity": "important",
      "content": "Avoid compact UVB bulbs and weak T8 fixtures for Uromastyx. They do not provide adequate UVB at safe distances."
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "heading": "UVB Placement Guidelines"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Distance and mesh coverage change UVB intensity. Place the basking platform at the correct distance for the chosen setup."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "<span class='text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white block mb-2'>Mounting Distance Guidelines:</span>"
    },
    {
